The paper discusses mobile sensor control for multi-target tracking in urban environments, which involves complex platform state dynamics and requires high-fidelity, non-myopic control strategies. This suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for tracking and sensor control. Additionally, the paper mentions the need for collaboration between the information fusion, tracking, and control research communities, indicating a systems (cs.SY) perspective. The use cases mentioned (person of interest, vehicle, and unauthorized UAV interdiction) also suggest a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cybersecurity (cs.CR) techniques.
